                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						                            
                            <p>Rājēndrachōḷa III. Year 33: 1279 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi> Vṛiśchika śu. 10, Monday, Uttiraṭṭādi are irregular.</p>						                            
                            <p>This inscription is damaged and mutilated. It seems to record a gift of land made tax-free by the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭavar</hi> of Umbaḷa-nāḍu, for [services] to the god and goddess in the temple.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
